{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a8f42b55-2008-45a6-966d-192f5d89eced",
    "name": "RFB-01 - Create Booking",
    "description": "## RFB-01 - Create Booking\n\nThis collection covers the **booking creation** flow for the Restful Booker API. It contains a suite of test cases that validate the `POST /booking` endpoint, ensuring it behaves correctly across both successful and error scenarios.\n\n### Test Cases\n\n| # | Test Case | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| TC-01 | Successful Booking Creation | Verifies that a booking is created successfully when all required fields are provided with valid data. |\n| TC-02 | Missing Required Fields | Validates that the API returns an appropriate error response when one or more required fields are omitted from the request. |\n| TC-03 | Invalid Date Format | Ensures the API correctly rejects requests where date fields are submitted in an unsupported or malformed format. |\n\n### Notes\n\n- All requests target the `{{baseUrl}}/booking/` endpoint.\n    \n- This collection is part of a broader QA automation suite for the Restful Booker API.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "23015621"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "TC-01 - Successful Booking Creation",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"TC-01 | Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"TC-01 | Response has bookingid\", function () {\r",
              "    var json = pm.response.json();\r",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"bookingid\");\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.bookingid).to.be.a(\"number\");\r",
              "    pm.environment.set(\"bookingId\", json.bookingid);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"TC-01 | Booking data matches request\", function () {\r",
              "    var json = pm.response.json().booking;\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.firstname).to.eql(\"John\");\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.lastname).to.eql(\"Doe\");\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.totalprice).to.eql(150);\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.depositpaid).to.eql(true);\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.bookingdates.checkin).to.eql(\"2026-03-20\");\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.bookingdates.checkout).to.eql(\"2026-03-25\");\r",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              ""
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\r\n  \"firstname\": \"John\",\r\n  \"lastname\": \"Doe\",\r\n  \"totalprice\": 150,\r\n  \"depositpaid\": true,\r\n  \"bookingdates\": {\r\n    \"checkin\": \"2026-03-20\",\r\n    \"checkout\": \"2026-03-25\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"additionalneeds\": \"Breakfast\"\r\n}",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/booking/",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "booking",
            ""
          ]
        },
        "description": "Create a booking with some informations successfully"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "TC-02 - Missing required fields",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('TC-02 | Status code is 200 (known bug RFB-18 — required fields not validated)', function () {\r",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test('TC-02 | Booking created despite missing firstname and lastname', function () {\r",
              "    var json = pm.response.json();\r",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('bookingid');\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.booking.firstname).to.eql('');\r",
              "    pm.expect(json.booking.lastname).to.eql('');\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "console.warn('TC-02: API accepts booking with missing firstname and lastname — known Restful Booker limitation. In a real API, a 400 should be returned. Documented in RFB-18.');"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\r\n  \"firstname\": \"\",\r\n  \"lastname\": \"\",\r\n  \"totalprice\": 150,\r\n  \"depositpaid\": true,\r\n  \"bookingdates\": {\r\n    \"checkin\": \"2026-03-20\",\r\n    \"checkout\": \"2026-03-25\"\r\n  }\r\n}",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/booking/",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "booking",
            ""
          ]
        },
        "description": "Create a booking with missing informations"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "TC-03 - Invalid date format",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"TC-03 | Status code is 400 - Invalid date format should be rejected\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"TC-03 | Response contains validation error message\", function () {\r",
              "    var json = pm.response.json();\r",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"error\");\r",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\r\n  \"firstname\": \"John\",\r\n  \"lastname\": \"Doe\",\r\n  \"totalprice\": 150,\r\n  \"depositpaid\": true,\r\n  \"bookingdates\": {\r\n    \"checkin\": \"27-03-2026\",\r\n    \"checkout\": \"25-03-2026\"\r\n  }\r\n}",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/booking/",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "booking",
            ""
          ]
        },
        "description": "Create a booking with invalid date format\n\n⚠️ This test is expected to FAIL. The API incorrectly accepts invalid date formats (DD-MM-YYYY) and returns 200 instead of 400. Defect tracked in RFB-17."
      },
      "response": []
    }
